# PAY-3811 — Stage QA (BMAD runbook)

**Status:** In Stage · Fix PR #290 (`f7e4af2e+`) · QA Chris (PAY-4011 / PAY-4012)  
**Full context:** `tickets/PAY-3811/PAY-3811-QA-Context.md`

## Critical link (why NULL-Token ACH fails)

Vault deactivates only when `Payment.Return.Received` carries **`TokenId`**. AchReturns sets it from the anchor charge:

`Guid.TryParse(payment.Token, out tokenId)` → if null/non-GUID → `TokenId=null` → vault **Acknowledge, no deactivation**.

**Tokenized for TC1** ⇔ `[Payments].[Payments].Token` (Platform charge row) = GUID equal to `TokenVault.dbo.BankAccountTokens.Id` with `Status=Active`.

Do **not** use random ACH `'000'` with `Token=NULL` — that only proves PAY-4047 ingest.

